How can you resize an EC2 instance, and what are the considerations when doing so?
You can resize an EC2 instance by stopping it, changing its instance type, and then starting it again.
However, itâ€™s essential to ensure that the new instance type meets your applicationâ€™s resource requirements
and that any instance-specific settings and data are preserved during the process.
=========================================================================================================================
What is an EC2 Spot Instance, and when would you use it?
An EC2 Spot Instance is a type of EC2 instance that allows you to bid on unused AWS capacity at significantly
reduced prices compared to On-Demand instances.
You would use Spot Instances for flexible, fault-tolerant applications that can handle interruptions,
such as big data processing, batch jobs, and background processing tasks.
They are ideal when cost savings are a priority, and your workload can tolerate potential instance termination.
