How does EC2 handle instance failures, and what strategies can you implement to ensure high availability for your applications?
Answer: EC2 instances can fail, but you can enhance availability by:
â€” Using Auto Scaling to automatically replace failed instances.
â€” Distributing your application across multiple Availability Zones.
â€” Implementing load balancing with Elastic Load Balancing (ELB).
â€” Utilizing Elastic IP addresses and DNS solutions for failover.
